Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows mild hypoglycemia, significantly elevated creatinine suggesting impaired renal function, low total CO₂ indicating possible metabolic acidosis, and mildly elevated ALT, which may reflect mild liver involvement. Other parameters are within normal limits. Renal function and acid-base status require urgent clinical correlation and further evaluation.
